article.headline: Lehigh 83, Army 64
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- C.J. McCollum scored 25 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead Lehigh over Army 83-64 on Sunday. McCollum now has 1,800 career points, moving past former Colgate standout Adonal Foyle for sixth in Patriot League history. The Mountain Hawks (17-6, 5-2) trailed 5-4 early and went on a 15-5 run to pull ahead for good, 19-10, on McCollum's free throw with 13:38 left in the first half. After Ella Ellis hit a layup for Army to make it a seven-point game, Lehigh scored 16 straight. Holden Greiner scored seven of his 14 points during the streak. The Mountain Hawks outrebounded Army 47-36 and scored 15 second-chance points. Lehigh won its third in a row and fifth of its last six. The Black Knights (10-12, 3-4) shot 39 percent (23 of 59), going 8 of 30 in the first half. Ellis led Army with 24 points and Milton Washington added 10.
